oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Rocky Mount, located near Piney Flats, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This site is the William Cobb farmstead in the western lands formerly part of North Carolina. As this area became settled, Congress created the Southwest Territory. William Blount lived here when he served as the Territorial Governor beginning in 1790.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Log buildings
